{"lemma":"سَعْدانٌ","slug":"سَعْدانٌ","root":"س.ع.د","root_slug":"س-ع-د","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ع-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19783","n19784"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"monkey, ape (mammal)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/saʕ.daːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19783","headword_ar":"سَعْدَانٌ","root":"sEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an augmentative letter, because there is not in the language any word of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolaAlN","text_ar":"فَعْلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xazoEaAlN","text_ar":"خَزْعَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qahoqaArN","text_ar":"قَهْقَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"unless it is of the reduplicative class, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"growing in the plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, tracts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the best kinds of the pastures of camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as long as it continues fresh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a head of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prickles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasakapu Als~aEodaAni","text_ar":"حَسَكَةُ السَّعْدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to which the nipple"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the areola"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a woman's breast is likened:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K: [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEodaAnapN","text_ar":"سَعْدَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below:]) the Arabs say that the camels that yield the sweetest milk are those that eat this plant: (TA:) and they fatten upon it: (Az, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is of the kind of plants called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoraAr","text_ar":"اَحْرَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hur~N","text_ar":"حُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slender, and succulent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sweet"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust-coloured, and sweet, and eaten by everything that is not large,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as well as by camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it is one of the most wholesome kinds of pasture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA:) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plant, having a round fruit with a prickly face, which, when it dries, falls upon the ground on its back, and when a person walking treads upon it, the prickles wound his foot: it is one of the best of their pastures in the days of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribyE","text_ar":"رِبيع"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sweetens the milk of the camels that feed upon it; for it is sweet as long as it continues fresh; and in this state men such it and eat it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, L:) the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroEFY walaA kaAls~aEodaAni","text_ar":"مَرْعًى وَلَا كَالسَّعْدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pasture, but not like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sEdAn","text_ar":"سعدان"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) said of a thing possessing excellence, but surpassed in excellence by another thing; or of a thing that excels other things of the like kind. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prickles of the palm-tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","T","Az","AHn","L"]},{"entry_id":"n19784","headword_ar":"سُعْدَانَ","root":"sEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAna","text_ar":"سُبْحَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is a name for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_isoEaAd","text_ar":"الاـِسْعَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of 4, and, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbHAn","text_ar":"سبحان"},{"kind":"text","text":", invariable, being put in the accus. case in the manner of an inf. n.]: one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAnahu wasuEodaAnahu","text_ar":"سُبْحَانَهُ وَسُعْدَانَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usab~iHuhu waA^uTiyEuhu","text_ar":"اُسَبِّحُهُ وَاُطِيعُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I declare,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"celebrate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extol, his"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. God's)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remoteness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"freedom, from every imperfection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impurity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., (see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbH","text_ar":"سبح"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and I render Him obedience,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aid his cause"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}